<item>
            <title>[DATAMONGO-446] Pageable query methods returning List are broken</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATAMONGO-446</link>
                <project id="10701" key="DATAMONGO">Spring Data MongoDB</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Documentation says that its possible to return &lt;tt&gt;List&lt;/tt&gt; for query methods with Pageable parameter. It works for Spring Data JPA but not for Spring Data MongoDB.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In order to fix that &lt;tt&gt;org.springframework.data.mongodb.repository.query.AbstractMongoQuery.CollectionExecution&lt;/tt&gt; could take provided &lt;tt&gt;Pageable&lt;/tt&gt; parameter (nullable) from &lt;tt&gt;MongoParametersParameterAccessor&lt;/tt&gt; and return paged result if pageable is not &lt;tt&gt;null&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Pull request is on its way.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
